         The Advanced Communications Technology Satellite (ACTS):  A Switchboard
         in the Sky
         full story
         ACTS Final Curtain Call
         Aerospace Frontiers, July, 2000
         "The ACTS Experiments Program has been an outstanding research and
         development achievement that resulted in a unique operational
         capability for the Center and the Agency," said NASA Glenn Research
         Center Director Donald J. Campbell.
         full story

         For ACTS Experiments-All Good Things Must Come to an End
         News Release, May 30, 2000
         "The ACTS Experiments Program has been an outstanding research and
         development achievement that resulted in a unique operational
         capability for the Center and the Agency," said Donald J. Campbell,
         NASA Glenn Research Center Director.  The ACTS Experiments Program has
         achieved remarkable milestones with 103 experiments and numerous
         demonstrations involving over 200 diverse partners, paving the way for
         the next generation of communications satellites.
         full story

         International Satellite Communications Conference to Highlight NASA
         ACTS Program
         Notes to Editors/News Directors, May 17, 2000
         Hundreds of members from the satellite industry are coming to
         Cleveland, Ohio to kick off the Sixth Annual International Ka-Band
         Utilization Conference with the NASA Glenn Research Center.  The first
         day is dedicated to NASA's Advanced Communications Technology.
         full story

         Congressional Record in Honor of ACTS
         Congressional Record, May 9, 2000
         A Congressional Record was written by Congressman Dennis Kucinich to
         salute the Advanced Communications Technology Satellite (ACTS).
         full story

         ACTS Experiments Conclusion
         March 6, 2000
         Notice about when the ACTS Experiments Program will come to an end.

         Changing the Way NASA and the Nation Communicates Through Space
         January 1st, 2000
         The Space Communications Program at Glenn Research Center provides
         research and development of space and air-based communication
         technologies.






